	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm pretty sure most FC carts have the same pinout as the NES, sometimes the ROM chips are directly the same (for old games).
<br />However don't take word of this as it, there may be differences, especially for board with weird names (like SL1ROM, etc...)
<br />
<br />Anyway the pinout of both mappers and FC cart connector is known, so you can just verify it with a beeping ohm meter yourself.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


