	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yes but some games changed from third party boards to nintendo boards in the us--castlevania 3 for example. They're few and far between, but they exist.
<br />
<br />The pinouts on official boards are the same, 3rd party boards aren't. I've made repros on famicom boards--only times I had to figure out pinouts were 3rd party boards. Do remember that the famicom chr and prg roms are on opposite sides of the circuit board.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

